’Ł@33b15b8b7b8cc48f8f1e57c3b5aa0b3d49c8b98d1703ce10a7fe52007e25dd3fŁ³Title: title: job spawn
Path: Examples
Content:
Spawn a background job to do some time consuming work.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> job spawn { sleep 5sec; rm evidence.pdf }


```
’Ł@d1e6b0d2b8ca5483d33d869ea377114ca3e15d2fecf7ae88dd34f54e3846e3aeŁžTitle: title: job spawn
Path: Notes
Content:
Executes the provided closure in a background thread

and registers this task in the background job table, which can be retrieved with 
``job list``
.
This command returns the job id of the newly created job.
